SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 5944
A bill to amend 1939 PA 280, entitled
"The social welfare act,"
(MCL 400.1 to 400.119b) by adding section 109y.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 109y. (1) The department shall provide coverage under the
2 medical assistance program to an eligible individual for behavioral
3 health transport.
4 (2) The department shall require a behavioral health transport
5 agency to comply with section 987 of the mental health code, 1974
6 PA 258, MCL 330.1987. The department shall reimburse a behavioral
7 health transport agency for providing behavioral transport to an
8 eligible individual only if the behavioral health transport is
9 ordered or certified by a licensed provider.
OOH H04157'25 (H-1) ma093d

2
1 (3) As used in this section:
2 (a) "Behavioral health transport" means that term as defined
3 in section 981 of the mental health code, 1974 PA 258, MCL
4 330.1981.
5 (b) "Behavioral health transport agency" means the owner or
6 operator of a behavioral health transport.
7 (c) "Eligible individual" means that term as defined in
8 section 981 of the mental health code, 1974 PA 258, MCL 330.1981.
9 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
10 unless Senate Bill No. 928 or House Bill No. 5943 of the 103rd
11 Legislature is enacted into law.
